data.name: Chasi
data.description:
Chasi helps equipment dealers grow and retain customers with 24/7 VIP treatment across all channels. Chasi’s AI agents act as executive assistants for sales and support reps, automating follow-ups, data collection, status updates, and outreach so teams can spend more time with customers and less on admin.

Over half of dealer payroll goes to sales and support, but a third of that team’s time is lost to admin. Fleets still run under 60% utilization, most branches lack after-hours coverage, and the aftermarket is largely reactive. Chasi plugs these revenue leaks by keeping units rented or sold, chasing every lead, and driving the right parts and service before machines fail.
data.one_liner: AI Concierge for Equipment sales, service & rentals

data.name: o11
data.description: o11 brings bulge bracket level speed and output quality to capital markets firms of any size. Seamlessly integrated into every Microsoft 365 tool, it transforms your documents and models into a dynamic knowledge layer that drives research, modeling, and client ready deliverables with consistent precision.
data.one_liner: The AI Platform for Capital Market Firms

data.name: Bubble Lab
data.description: Bubble Lab is an open-source Typescript-native workflow automation platform. Unlike tools that use proprietary JSON, you describe a workflow in natural language, and instantly get both a visual flow and fully-typed TypeScript code side-by-side. It offers built-in observability, testability, and scalability out of the box.
data.one_liner: Open-source, Typescript-native agentic workflow builder

data.name: Pocket
data.description: Pocket is a tiny AI device that lives on your phone and turns everything you say and hear into clear notes, action items, and search. We combine custom hardware, AI, and software to build the best note-taking experience for people who talk and move fast
data.one_liner: The world's best AI note-taking device and app

data.name: Constellation
data.description: ConstellationOS uses environmental and antenna telemetry to predict satellite link failures before they happen. By shifting ground stations from reactive emergency handoffs to proactive scheduling, we eliminate manual overhead and the high cost of data loss for satellite operators.
data.one_liner: AI for satellite mission assurance.

data.name: AxionOrbital Space
data.description:
AxionOrbital Space builds foundation models that enable continuous visibility through clouds and darkness. Legacy optical satellites are rendered useless 70% of the time by weather and night cycles, while Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) produces data that is unintelligible to humans and breaks standard vision pipelines.

We solve this by translating raw radar backscatter into analysis-ready optical imagery in real-time. Our proprietary architecture uses deterministic one-step diffusion to transform complex radar signals into clear, photorealistic images. This enables persistent, 24/7 situational awareness for defense, commodities trading, and disaster response, guaranteeing visibility even when the sky is blocked.
data.one_liner: Foundation models for 24/7 Earth Observation

data.name: Caretta
data.description:
Caretta is a Sales Intelligence for revenue teams. It joins reps in live calls, helping them handle information requests, questions, and objections in real time. Caretta lives in Slack to join the team conversation.

Caretta gets smarter automatically: every call expands its knowledge base and objection library, turning conversations into compounding organizational advantage.
data.one_liner: 24/7 Sales Intelligence

data.name: Ressl AI
data.description:
Ressl AI is building AI Agents to disrupt IT Services.

Enterprise applications like Salesforce are highly flexible and configurable, allowing them to adapt to the unique processes of different businesses. But implementing and maintaining Salesforce requires specialised Salesforce admins or outsourced consulting firms—both of which are expensive and slow.

At Ressl AI, we’re building 10× AI Salesforce Admins. Our agents let IT and RevOps teams configure Salesforce in plain English, accelerating Salesforce delivery by 10× without adding headcount.

Our agents can:

> Document your Salesforce org
> Find root causes of support issues
> Perform analysis and dependency mapping
> Configure flows and automations
> Write Apex code and test classes
> Upgrade orgs from legacy versions

Before building Ressl, Arushi and Abhishek ran an IT consulting firm for six months, using those learnings to productise RevOps and Salesforce consulting.

The global IT outsourcing market is projected to reach ~$600B in 2025. Ressl AI is excited to define what an agentic Accenture looks like.
data.one_liner: AI Agents for ERP / CRM Configuration, starting with Salesforce

data.name: Patientdesk.ai
data.description: The universal AI front desk for healthcare: plugs into any practice management system (cloud-based or on-premise) and automates all patient workflows: scheduling, cancellations, payment plans, insurance checks, reminders, intake, and follow-ups.
data.one_liner: AI voice agent for patient calls & admin workflows

data.name: Prana
data.description:
Prana replaces the reactive, 15-minute annual physical with continuous, proactive care. We connect to your medical records and wearables to watch for "clinical drift," catching subtle declines in health that human doctors miss between visits.

Most AI health apps are just chatbots. Prana is a full-stack medical provider. Our AI acts as a always-on physician that watches your data, explains your labs, and manages your prescriptions.

Safety & Scale: We automate 90% of the "grunt work" (history taking, logistics, triage) so our human doctors can focus purely on high-leverage decisions. This allows us to offer <60 minute access to a physician, 24/7, for a fraction of the cost of traditional care.

The Team:
 - Meer Patel (CEO): JHU BME. Deferred Brown Medical School to build Prana because code scales better than appointments.
- Vishvam Rawal (CTO): Ex-Quant. Building high-frequency data infrastructure for health signals.
- Sanjit Menon (CMO): Graduating MD Candidate. Deep clinical expertise to ensure our models practice good medicine.

Traction: Live in beta with early users.
data.one_liner: An AI primary care doctor in your pocket

data.name: Luel
data.description: Luel is the go-to market for fast, rights-cleared multimodal training data at scale. We work with AI teams to provide bespoke data collections sourced from our global network of vetted contributors and off-the-shelf datasets. With our efficient contributor pipeline and multi-stage QA pipeline, we cut out slow vendor processes and deliver on-spec data with full provenance.
data.one_liner: Turning everyday words and actions into usable training data.

data.name: Skillsync
data.description: Skillsync helps companies find engineers based on their code. It creates structured skill profiles of developers based on their open source contributions on GitHub. Using a Cursor-like interface, companies can search for specific capabilities like "deployed custom neural nets on edge" then qualify, shortlist and engage with engineers already building in their domain.
data.one_liner: Find anyone in open source

data.name: MirageDoodle, Inc.
data.description:
At MirageDoodle, we’re building coordinated AI agents that live inside cities’ cross-department development review workflows—doing the heavy lifting, escalating judgment calls, and letting staff focus where human expertise actually matters.

MirageDoodle provides expert-level guidance in minutes based on precedents, helping cities and design firms navigate an increasingly complex, fragmented regulatory environment

We serve as strategic partners to forward-thinking cities and design firms across the country.
data.one_liner: AI-native workspace for municipal development review

data.name: 21st
data.one_liner: Product design and prototyping tool for AI native teams

data.name: Avoice
data.description: Avoice brings your studio’s work together on one intelligent platform that automates the parts of practice that drain time from design. It understands your sheets, specs, schedules, materials, codes, and past projects, allowing precise automation across documentation, coordination, QA/QC, and research. Avoice also transforms your firm’s design knowledge and material libraries into a connected and searchable system that preserves standards and elevates consistency. With every document, workflow, and insight in one place, tasks that once took hours now take moments, giving your team more clarity, more momentum, and more room for meaningful architectural work.
data.one_liner: The AI Workspace For Architects

data.name: LegalOS
data.description:
LegalOS is an AI-powered immigration law firm for complex U.S. work visas. 

Our AI agents generate a USCIS-ready petition package in 24–48 hours, including forms, support letters, and a structured evidence memo.

Every case is reviewed and signed by licensed immigration attorneys with 40+ years of experience and a near-100% approval rate, so companies get both speed and reliability. LegalOS already supports O-1, H-1B, L-1A, L-1B, TN, EB-1A, EB-1C, and EB-2 NIW petitions and has a 100% approval rate so far across all visa categories.
data.one_liner: The AI-powered immigration law firm for complex work visas

data.name: Sonarly
data.description:
We'd like to automate monitoring. To advance that mission, we're building Sonarly.

Coding agents are amazingly good at building software. But they struggle fixing production bugs because they lack the right context for them. We give them that context, eliminating the time you spend on bug detection, session replay, issue description, and endlessly copy-pasting logs to your AI agent.
data.one_liner: Production-bug context for AI agents

data.name: Didit
data.description: Didit is an AI-native, developer-first identity verification platform that makes KYC, AML, and fraud prevention instant, flexible, and transparent, with a seamless user experience and more than 70% lower costs.
data.one_liner: AI-native, developer-first identity verification platform

data.name: Hlabs
data.description:
Robotics is going to be one of the largest industries the world has ever seen, but right now teams have to build so much in house just to get something to move. Hlabs is making a plug-and-play ecosystem of robotic parts with simple opensource software libraries to reduce the complexity in building a robot.

Hlabs is founded by Paul, a second time YC founder who also participated in the W21 batch with Mystic. He ran Mystic as CEO for 6 years.

From the first launch in October 2025 over 40 robotics companies have placed orders for the actuator control product. Hlabs is targeting Q1 '26 for the release of several additional plug-and-play products including an Nvidia Jetson powered main board, a low cost expandable camera system, and wireless communication/video module to make every robot wireless out of the box.
data.one_liner: Developer friendly robotics

data.name: Valgo
data.description:
As autonomy moves into complex safety-critical domains (e.g., aviation), failures become more costly and companies must devote significant in-house effort to validate their system before real-world deployment. Valgo accelerates autonomous systems development and certification by providing tooling to perform algorithmic safety validation at scale. We are building a platform to efficiently find rare and realistic failure events in simulation at a fraction of the compute cost required by existing approaches. Our tools are agnostic to models/simulators (i.e., black box) and can be applied across industries such as autonomous vehicles, aviation, robotics, space, defense, energy, and finance.

Valgo was founded by Stanford PhDs who wrote the textbook and taught the course at Stanford on algorithmic safety validation. We also have significant industry experience working on an FAA-certified collision avoidance system at MIT Lincoln Laboratory, validating autonomous aircraft at Xwing, and collaborating with industry sponsors across transportation, aviation, and energy.
data.one_liner: Algorithmic safety validation tools for autonomy.

data.name: Sarah AI
data.description:
Sarah AI is building the AI-native operating system for consumer goods brands—an autonomous supply-chain brain that replaces legacy ERPs and actually runs the business. Founded by Chris (2x Founder; ex-CEO at Better Nature; Forbes 30U30) and Dirk (ex-Google Data, Analytics & AI Lead), we’re backed by YC (W26).

In our first month full-time, we’ve raised $1.6M and secured rapid commercial traction with 15 design partners and a growing pipeline of 30+ brands. Our mission is bold: give CPG brands completely hands-free supply chains that run themselves through Sarah, their AI ops assistant.

We’re now growing a small, world-class team of builders excited to reinvent how physical goods companies operate—end-to-end, autonomous, and AI-first. If you want to work on hard problems, ship fast, and define the future of autonomous operations, you’ll feel right at home here.
data.one_liner: AI Agents for CPG ops

data.name: Mantis Biotechnology
data.description:
Mantis provides the foundational infrastructure layer that enables companies to build human-in-computer models. We unify fragmented data sources, simulate human anatomy and physiology, and validate against real-world outcomes.

From motion capture and biometric sensors to medical imaging and training logs, our platform transforms disparate data into validated digital twins ready for production applications.
data.one_liner: The Infrastructure Powering Human-In-Computer Models

data.name: Voltair
data.description:
Voltair builds drones that ‘perch’ like birds to recharge on power lines. The grid is the world’s largest machine. This allows our flying robots to go anywhere. Simply put, removing battery swaps is the last step to deploy UAVs autonomously at scale. After building drones for the Air Force and DARPA, Ronan realized this was both practical and technically feasible.

Power utilities are the perfect first customer. From talking to 50+ power utilities (including our 3 customers), it’s clear that they need better tech to observe their 1000+ miles of line. A given utility pole is inspected about once a decade.

Why is this timeline a problem? Inspections identify maintenance concerns before they cause faults. Faults cause power outages, and spark wildfires - like the Eaton Fire in early 2025 where 19 people lost their lives and nearly 10,000 structures were destroyed. Fires bankrupt utilities and make them uninsurable. Autonomous drones can deliver over 20x the inspection coverage for the same cost.

Reducing wildfire risk is a top priority for our customers, and utilities already know drones are the best solution (early pilots find over 5x more maintenance concerns with drones than ground inspections). Hayden knows this best. He worked in system protection at a power utility throughout college.

We’re operating as a full-stack power utility asset inspection contractor. Since June, we’ve validated our core charging tech on a power line, built 5x flying prototypes, and inspected ~2000 poles. We’re post-revenue.

There’s 168M poles in the US. Going rates for inspections are ~$45/pole, a $7.6B market. The horizontals for a system of drones distributed on the grid are massive. Our drones are inexpensive (<$5k), so our margins look like a SaaS company.

At scale we are a new infrastructure layer for data on the physical world.
data.one_liner: Self Charging Drones

data.name: Oxus
data.description:
Oxus is the AI-native platform modernizing internal audits. We turn hours of manual scoping, documentation, and control testing into review-ready outputs generated within minutes.
 
With Oxus, audit teams deliver more audits, faster.
data.one_liner: AI-powered automation for internal audit workflows

data.name: Travo
data.description:
We are building the most accurate and comprehensive real estate data set for RV parks and similar niche asset classes.

Travo is the one stop shop for anyone working in real estate to search any property or parcel of land and instantly access rental comps, ownership, zoning and financials. With our data, we build the best informed AI applications for real estate private equity firms, developers, and brokers.
data.one_liner: We use AI to collect and analyze real estate data
